
The purpose of this study was to investigate changes in the spatial distribution of cortical activity associated with zzso treatment in three persons with zzso Participants underwent three zzso sessions before and after a period of intensive language treatment focused on object zzso The results revealed bilateral zzso recruitment associated with improved ability to name items targeted in zzso This is the first study to employ multiple zzso and zzso zzso sessions in the study of zzso recovery from zzso and has implications for future studies of brain plasticity in zzso 

